The paper deals with joint source-channel coding, channel coding, and source coding, which are all topics related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses optimization problems and LP relaxations, which are common in optimization and mathematical programming (cs.ITP). The paper mentions the use of Hamming distortion, which is a measure of error in digital communication and is relevant to multimedia systems (cs.MM). The paper also discusses multi-terminal settings, which are relevant to networked systems (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the successive refinement problem, which is a topic in machine learning and data compression (cs.LG).
